OpenFlow.NBAPI
Interface ReceivedMessageCallPrep

public interface ReceivedMessageCallPrep

Preparation call for NB API message-received call-back.

This is an optional interface that an implementor of ReceivedMessageCall may also implement.

Method Summary

Method Detail

receivedMessagePrep

void receivedMessagePrep(ReceivedMessageEvent event)
Preparation call for message-received call-back.

The contract for this method is that it will not significantly delay processing, as it is run as part of the message dispatcher's thread rather than the call-back thread. It is guaranteed that the preparation calls will all be made prior to the completion of the dispatch, so that any threads added to the ReceivedMessageEvent.app_map will be run.
